    <measure>The degree of disability progression from baseline as measured by the Expanded Disability Status Scale (EDSS).</measure>
    <time_frame>Up to week 24</time_frame>
    <description>The EDSS measures disability status on a scale ranging from 0 to 10, with higher scores indicating more disability. Scoring is based on measures of impairment in eight functional systems on examination by a neurologist. Disability is measured as at least a 1.0-point increase on the EDSS from baseline EDSS â‰¥1.0 that is sustained for 24 weeks, or at least a 1.5-point increase on the EDSS from baseline EDSS = 0 that is sustained for 24 weeks.</description>
